<div style=3D"float: right;padding-top:2pt"></div><h1 id=3D"hid1" class=3D"=
section">Rank of a matrix</h1>
<p class=3D"author">by <span itemprop=3D"author" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D=
"https://schema.org/Person"><a class=3D"author" id=3D"article-author" href=
=3D"https://www.statlect.com/about/#author">Marco Taboga</a></span>, PhD</p=
>
<p>
   The column rank of a
    <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/vectors-and-matrices=
">matrix</a> is the
    <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/dimension-of-a-linea=
r-space">dimension of the linear
   space</a> spanned by its columns.
</p>
<p>
   The row rank of a matrix is the dimension of the space spanned by its ro=
ws.
</p>
<p>
   Since we can prove that the row rank and the column rank are always equa=
l, we
   simply speak of the rank of a matrix.
</p>



<p><img width=3D"29" height=3D"24" src=3D"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgo=
AAAANSUhEUgAAAB0AAAAYCAIAAACJPGHrAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAA=
