<h2 id=3D"hid2" class=3D"subsection">Column rank</h2>
<p>
   Let us start with a definition.
</p>
<div class=3D"definition">
   <p><span class=3D"titoletto">Definition</span>
      Let
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"A" style=3D"background-position:0px -2059px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>
      be a
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"40" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$K	imes L$" style=3D"background-position:0px -1375p=
x;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      matrix. The column rank of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"A" style=3D"background-position:0px -2059px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>
      is<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp2" width=3D"271" height=
=3D"41" src=3D"https://www.statlect.com/images/rank-of-a-matrix__4.png" alt=
=3D"[eq1]"></span>where
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"22" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$A_{=08ullet l}$" style=3D"background-position:0px =
-1816px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      denotes the
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"7" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$l$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2303px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>-th
      column of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"A" style=3D"background-position:0px -2059px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>,
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"31" height=3D"26" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$QTR{rm}{span}$" style=3D"background-position:0px -=
1593px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      denotes the  <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/linea=
r-span">linear span</a>, and
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"25" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$dim $" style=3D"background-position:0px -1619px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>
      denotes the
       <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/dimension-of-a-li=
near-space">dimension</a>.
   </p>
</div>
<p>
   Remember that the dimension of a
    <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/linear-spaces">linea=
r space</a> is the number of
   elements of one of its
    <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/basis-of-a-linear-sp=
ace">bases</a>, that is, the
   number of  <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/linear-ind=
ependence">linearly
   independent</a> vectors that generate the space. So, the column rank of =
a
   matrix is the number of linearly independent vectors that generate the s=
ame
   space generated by the columns of the matrix.
</p>
<div class=3D"example">
   <p><span class=3D"titoletto">Example</span>
      Consider the matrix
      <span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"135" height=3D"7=
7" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAA=
BAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq2]" style=3D"background-position:0px -420p=
x;"></span>and
      the linear space
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2278px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>
      spanned by its two
      columns<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp2" width=3D"253" hei=
ght=3D"77" src=3D"https://www.statlect.com/images/rank-of-a-matrix__12.png"=
 alt=3D"[eq3]"></span>that
      is, the space of all vectors that can be written as
       <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/linear-combinatio=
ns">linear combinations</a> of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"25" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$A_{=08ullet 1}$" style=3D"background-position:0px =
-1718px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      and
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"25" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$A_{=08ullet 2}$" style=3D"background-position:0px =
-1693px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>.
      Any vector
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"38" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$sin S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -1472px;v=
ertical-align:-5px"></span>
      can be written
      as<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"139" height=3D=
"41" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAA=
AABAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq4]" style=3D"background-position:0px -37=
9px;"></span>where
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"20" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$=07lpha _{1}$" style=3D"background-position:0px -1=
866px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      and
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"20" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$=07lpha _{2}$" style=3D"background-position:0px -1=
841px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      are two scalars. Note that the two columns
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"25" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$A_{=08ullet 1}$" style=3D"background-position:0px =
-1718px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      and
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"25" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$A_{=08ullet 2}$" style=3D"background-position:0px =
-1693px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>
      are linearly dependent
      because<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"99" heigh=
t=3D"41" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAAL=
AAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq5]" style=3D"background-position:0px=
 -1005px;"></span>Therefore,
      any vector
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"38" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$sin S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -1472px;v=
ertical-align:-5px"></span>
      can be written as a multiple of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"25" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$A_{=08ullet 1}$" style=3D"background-position:0px =
-1644px;vertical-align:-5px"></span>:
      <span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"169" height=3D"9=
3" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAA=
BAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq6]" style=3D"background-position:0px -80px=
;"></span>As
      a consequence,
      <span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"86" height=3D"41=
" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAAB=
AAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq7]" style=3D"background-position:0px -1160p=
x;"></span>is
      a basis for
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2278px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>.
      It has
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"1" style=3D"background-position:0px -2205px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>
      element. Therefore, the dimension of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2278px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>
      and the column rank of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"A" style=3D"background-position:0px -2059px;vertica=
